<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.158387>
    bibo:endPage "7" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "614" ;
    dc:creator "Bravo, Freddy" ;
    dc:date "2004" ;
    dc:title "Maruina guria (Diptera, Psychodidae), a new psychodid species from Brazil" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.158388>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.158389> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.158388>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 6. Maruina guria Bravo, sp. nov. Holotype male. 1. Head. 2. Base of antenna (scape, pedicel and three flagellomeres). 3. Flagellomere 7 showing one ascoid. 4. alpus. 5. Wing. 6. Abdomen showing sclerotized internal areas and tuft of bristles in sternites 6 and 8. (S 6 = sternite 6; S 8 = sternite 8)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/158388/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.158389>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7 – 10. Maruina guria Bravo, sp. nov. 7 – 9. (holotype) male. 10. (allotype) female. 7. Male terminalia lateral. 8. Male terminalia: tergite 9 and sternite 10. 9. Male terminalia dorsal. 10. Female terminalia. (S 9 = sternite 9; S 10 = sternite 10)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/158389/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

